Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of evolutionary algorithms for bi-level optimization problems, which are combinatorial optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques, such as evolutionary algorithms, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of the runtime complexity of the algorithms, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of two NP-hard problems, which could also fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
